data.text:
Madhuri Dixit and Shriram Nene, Shahid Kapoor and family's lunch outing in Bandra

Madhuri Dixit Nene along with husband Sriram Nene was spotted at a popular restaurant in Bandra, Mumbai. Madhuri looked pretty in her pink and white traditional attire, while Shriram wore formals. All pictures/Yogen Shah

After announcing her second Marathi production titled Panchak with husband Dr. Shriram Nene, Madhuri Dixit Nene launched her Youtube Channel in October. Through it, the ace actress promises her fans a glimpse into her personal life.

Shahid Kapoor along with wife Mira and daughter Misha were spotted at a popular restaurant in Bandra-Kurla-Complex. The Kabir Singh actor has already started prep for his next film, Hindi remake of Telegu film Jersey.

Shahid Kapoor has started training to hone his cricketing skills for the role of a cricketer in the movie. Jersey will be directed by Gowtam Tinnanauri who helmed the original as well. Produced by Allu Aravind, Aman Gill, Dil Raju, the film is scheduled to release on August 28, 2020.

Jacqueline Fernandez was spotted in Bandra. Recently, Jacqueline took to social media to share her 'fan moment' with Katy Perry who is visiting India for a music festival. Jacqueline shares in an interview, "She is very interested in Bollywood and in watching a couple of movies. When she asked me to recommend one, I suggested Kick. It’s really sweet that she wants to understand the culture and immerse herself into some Bollywood films."

Soha Ali Khan and Ashish Choudhary attended the launch of Voot Kids App at a plush hotel in Juhu.
